x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ole Solberg","active":true},"body":"A similar(?) failure still shows up on vista/1.4.2. \r\nSee e.g. http://dbtg.thresher.com/derby/test/Daily/jvm1.4/testing/Limited/testSummary-596365.html / vista,\r\nor via todays http://dbtg.thresher.com/derby/test/stats_today.html .\r\n\r\n1) testDefault(org.apache.derbyTesting.functionTests.tests.engine.ErrorStreamTest)junit.framework.AssertionFailedError: assertNotEmpty failed:C:\\cludev\\jagtmp\\autoderbyN_derbyall\\suitesAll_1\\log\\system\\derby.log\r\n2) testFile(org.apache.derbyTesting.functionTests.tests.engine.ErrorStreamTest)junit.framework.AssertionFailedError: assertNotEmpty failed:C:\\cludev\\jagtmp\\autoderbyN_derbyall\\suitesAll_1\\log\\system\\file-2.log\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=olesolberg","name":"olesolberg","emailAddress":"Ole dot Solberg at Sun dot COM","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ole Solberg","active":true},"created":"2007-11-20T14:57:39.357+0000","updated":"2007-11-20T15:26:07.627+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12382405/comment/12544454","id":"12544454","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"body":"It is most likely a different issue, and I'm a bit surprised it only happens on Vista with a 1.4 JVM, and not in any other configuration. I'll find a Vista machine and see if I can figure it out.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"created":"2007-11-21T13:17:20.075+0000","updated":"2007-11-21T13:17:20.075+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12382405/comment/12545414","id":"12545414","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"body":"I think we have hit a bug in the 1.4.2 JDK on Vista. Derby specifically creates a PrintWriter with automatic flushing enabled for writing to derby.log, but in this test nothing is flushed to derby.log before the engine is shut down.\r\n\r\nThe nightly testing is run with update 13 of Suns 1.4.2 JDK, I'll try update 16 and see if it is fixed there. If it fails there as well I am not sure what we can do about this problem.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"created":"2007-11-26T11:49:14.515+0000","updated":"2007-11-26T11:49:14.515+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12382405/comment/12545445","id":"12545445","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"body":"This also fails with the latest available update (16) of Suns JDK1.4.2 on Vista. I've logged the bug against the jdk, but this test will keep failing the way things are now.\r\n\r\nI'm unsure about how to best handle this. Since the test only fails with jdk1.4.2 on Vista, the bug does not create a lot of noise and the test works on all other platforms/jdks. I also consider the fact that logmessages are flushed immediately a part of Derbys functionality and not an implementation detail, so I think the test is valid the way it is. Any precedent for how cases like this one are handled?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"created":"2007-11-26T13:49:20.075+0000","updated":"2007-11-26T13:49:20.075+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12382405/comment/12545758","id":"12545758","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"body":"This patch changes the ErrorStream test to avoid the problematic piece of code (File.length() checks) when running on Windows Vista with Sun JDK 1.4.2, for all other configurations it should behave the same way as before. This should remove the \"noise\" from the nightly testing.\r\n\r\nI have also changed the setup of the tests a little to be more robust if any of the tests fail.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":t