ure if it is File.length() that is buggy or if the output isn't flushed, I'll try your suggestion and see if that works.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"created":"2007-11-27T09:35:29.682+0000","updated":"2007-11-27T09:35:29.682+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12382405/comment/12545779","id":"12545779","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Vemund Ã˜stgaard","active":true},"body":"That certainly was a better solution, apparently the flushing works fine it is just File.length() that is buggy in certain circumstances. \r\n\r\nHere is a new patch using your approach instead. Hopefully this works on all other configurations as well, I tested a few and it looked good.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vemund","name":"vemund","emailAddress":"vemund at sun dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https